net.commerce.zocalo.currency
Class CouponBank

java.lang.Object
  net.commerce.zocalo.currency.CouponBank
Direct Known Subclasses:
UnaryCouponBank
public class CouponBank
extends java.lang.Object

CouponBank is an issuer of Coupons for a particular claim. It issues a non-forgeable currency, and is the only holder of the token that allows creation of new Coupons. Anyone who has access to the bank can instruct the bank to issue coupon pairs or individual coupons. The pairs must be paid for, so that interface doesn't need to be closely held, but the ability to create unpaired coupons must be treated as a closely held capability.
